{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01A9hX2ALSuBch9N1TvuXNTK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. I need to build `src/tx-builder.ts` that:\n\n1. Builds a `create_match` instruction using the coinflip IDL\n2. Sets creator wallet as fee payer\n3. Server keypair as `server` signer\n4. Passes commitment + tier + side + nonce as args\n5. Partially signs with server keypair\n6. Returns base64-serialized transaction + match PDA\n7. Fetches recent blockhash at build time\n\nI need to decide how to build the instruction. Options:\n1. Use `@coral-xyz/anchor` Program class with the IDL\n\n\n2. Use raw `@solana/web3.js` TransactionInstruction with the discriminator from the IDL\n\nSince the backend is a lightweight service, I should keep it simple. The IDL has the discriminator `[107, 2, 184, 145, 70, 142, 17, 165]` for `create_match`. I could use the Anchor Program class for easier serialization and account layout handling, but that's a heavier dependency. Let me check what dependencies are already available in the package.\n\nLooking at the package.json, `@solana/web3.js` is there but `@coral-xyz/anchor` isn't. I could either add it or manually construct the instruction with borsh serialization, though that's more error-prone. Given that the spec explicitly mentions using the coinflip IDL, I think the right call is to add `@coral-xyz/anchor` and use it to consume the IDL JSON directly for constructing the instruction properly.\n\nI need to check what version the monorepo is using, and I'm also remembering some important gotchas: `@coral-xyz/anchor` doesn't export `BN` as a named ESM export, so I'll need to destructure it from the default import, and Anchor's Borsh serializer specifically requires `BN` from bn.js rather than native JavaScript `BigInt`.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6157